# Cursor Rules
# Place this file at: .cursorrules in project root

# Governance: Follow all rules in /path/to/ai-governance-framework/RULES.md
# Follow the Interaction Protocol in /path/to/ai-governance-framework/INTERACTION_PROTOCOL.md
# All rules are mandatory. Categories (Critical/High/Standard/Behavioral) indicate impact, not priority.
# Never paste credentials, PII, or proprietary data. See SELF_GOVERNANCE.md.
# Match AI execution environment to data sensitivity. Never process sensitive data through public AI.
# Use only approved tools and accounts for work data. No personal AI accounts or unapproved extensions.
# AI assists decisions — humans are accountable. AI output is not the sole basis for high-impact decisions.

# === RULES ===

# 1. No hard-coded values — use env vars, database, or config files
# 2. No credentials in code — use env vars or credential store
# 3. Parameterized SQL only — never string concatenation
# 4. UUIDs in URLs/APIs — never numeric database IDs
# 5. Use existing components — search before creating
# 6. Follow project patterns — match established conventions
# 7. No duplication — reuse, extract shared utilities
# 8. Security first — OWASP Top 10, sanitize input, handle errors
# 9. Verify all output — treat AI suggestions as untrusted

# === CODE STYLE ===

# - One component per file
# - Files under 300 lines
# - Descriptive names, comment "why" not "what"
# - Handle all error cases explicitly
# - Never swallow exceptions silently

# === BEFORE WRITING CODE ===

# - Read existing code in the relevant files first
# - Check for existing shared components
# - Identify all files that need to change
# - Follow the pre-coding checklist in .ai-gov/RULES.md

# === TESTING ===

# - Every change must be verified end-to-end
# - Code compiling is NOT verification
# - Test in actual UI, check persistence, verify no regressions

# === PRODUCTION ===

# - Never modify production data or code without explicit confirmation
# - READ-ONLY default on all production systems
# - Deployments require rollback plan

# Read /path/to/ai-governance-framework/RULES.md for the complete rule set.
# A task is only complete at Level 5 verification (end-to-end workflow). Levels 1-4 are progress, not completion.

# === USER VERIFICATION (Tier B fallback) ===
# Cursor's enforcement is Tier B (context-file). If the AI's first response does
# not include the governance audit block, the user must follow the recovery reply
# in /path/to/ai-governance-framework/USER_VERIFICATION.md.
